name: ipc.[port_number].decay-scheduler.period-ms
description:
How frequently the decay factor should be applied to the
    operation counts of users. Higher values have less overhead, but respond
    less quickly to changes in client behavior.
    This property applies to DecayRpcScheduler.

name: mapreduce.jobhistory.joblist.cache.size
description: Size of the job list cache

name: mapreduce.job.maxtaskfailures.per.tracker
description:
The number of task-failures on a node manager of a given job
               after which new tasks of that job aren't assigned to it. It
               MUST be less than mapreduce.map.maxattempts and
               mapreduce.reduce.maxattempts otherwise the failed task will
               never be tried on a different node.

name: dfs.client.retry.max.attempts
description: Max retry attempts for DFSClient talking to namenodes.

name: hadoop.security.kms.client.encrypted.key.cache.num.refill.threads
description:
Number of threads to use for refilling depleted EncryptedKeyVersion
    cache Queues

name: dfs.datanode.max.disks.to.report
description:
Number of disks to include in JSON report per operation. We will return
    disks with the highest latency.

name: dfs.namenode.snapshot.max.limit
description:
Limits the maximum number of snapshots allowed per snapshottable
    directory.If the configuration is not set, the default limit
    for maximum no of snapshots allowed is 65536.

name: mapreduce.jobhistory.datestring.cache.size
description:
Size of the date string cache. Effects the number of directories
  which will be scanned to find a job.
